title: Champions and finalists of UEFA EURO championship 1960 to 2016
summary: This grouped bar chart represents 13 different Countrys on X-axis for 2 groups Winner, and Runner-up. On the Y-axis it shows their corresponding SOME LABEL.
Out of all 2 groups, Winner had the highest SOME LABEL in Country Spain and Winner had the lowest SOME LABEL in Country Yugoslavia.
Among all the Countrys, Runner-up had the highest SOME LABEL 3.0 in Country USSR and lowest value 0.0 in Country Czechoslovakia.
Country USSR and Czechoslovakia had the biggest gap of 3.0 between the highest and lowest SOME LABEL found for Runner-up.

max_summary: This grouped bar chart shows SOME LABEL on the Y-axis for 13 different Countrys for 2 groups Winner, and Runner-up that are presented on the X-axis.
In Country Spain, Winner had the highest SOME LABEL 3.0 among the 2 groups and in Yugoslavia, Winner had the lowest SOME LABEL 0.0.
In Country USSR, Runner-up had the highest SOME LABEL among all 13 Countrys and it has the lowest SOME LABEL in Country Czechoslovakia.
Country USSR and Czechoslovakia had the biggest gap of 3.0 between the highest and lowest SOME LABEL found for Runner-up.
Out of all 2 groups, the highest gap between the maximum and minimum SOME LABEL was found in case of Winner.
Averaging all 2 groups Winner, and Runner-up, the Country Germany is the maximum SOME LABEL and Czechoslovakia is the minimum SOME LABEL.
